# Development Environment Setup

## Prerequisites
- Node.js (latest LTS version)
- Docker and Docker Compose
- MongoDB (local or Docker)
- Git

## Local Development
1. Frontend development runs on Vite dev server
2. Backend uses Express with Node.js
3. TypeScript is used for type safety
4. Tailwind CSS for styling

## Docker Development
- Use Docker Compose for local development
- Frontend and backend are containerized
- MongoDB can be run in Docker
- PM2 manages Node.js processes

## Production Deployment
- Ubuntu Server environment
- Nginx reverse proxy configuration
- SSL/TLS via Let's Encrypt
- UFW firewall rules
- Dynamic DNS setup for home hosting

## Monitoring Setup
- Uptime Kuma for availability monitoring
- Netdata for system metrics
- Logrotate for log management

For detailed configuration, see [Tech-stack.md](mdc:memory-bank/Tech-stack.md)
